# component-contracts — Agent Rules

These rules apply to every task in this repository. Read them before making any changes.

---

## Core principle

**Contracts are authored before implementations.** Never write a component implementation
without a corresponding `.contract.json` in `packages/contracts/src/`. The contract is the
source of truth. All outputs — React, Web Components, iOS, Android, Figma — are derived from it.

---

## Atomic Design

Structure all components according to Atomic Design:

- **Atoms** — single-purpose, no dependencies on other components (Button, Icon, Badge, Input)
- **Molecules** — composed of atoms, single responsibility (Accordion, SearchInput, FormField)
- **Organisms** — composed of molecules and atoms, complex UI sections (Header, DataTable, Form)
- **Templates / Pages** — layout-level, not part of this library

When authoring a contract, declare the atomic level in the `description` field. When
implementing, place the component at the correct level:

```
apps/web/src/
  atoms/
    button/
    icon/
    badge/
  molecules/
    accordion/
    form-field/
  organisms/
    ...
```

---

## Token architecture (3 tiers — enforced)

- **Tier 1 Primitives** — `packages/tokens/src/primitive/*.tokens.json` — raw values only
- **Tier 2 Semantic** — `packages/tokens/src/semantic/semantic.tokens.json` — aliases into Tier 1
- **Tier 3 Component** — `packages/tokens/src/component/{id}.tokens.json` — aliases into Tier 2

Components (CSS, Figma, native) consume **only Tier 3 tokens**. Never reference Tier 1 or
Tier 2 directly in a component. Contracts reference Tier 3 token names in their `tokens` section.

Adding a component requires all four of these together — no partial updates:
1. Contract (`.contract.json`)
2. Component token file (`packages/tokens/src/component/{id}.tokens.json`)
3. CSS update (component consumes `--ds-{component}-*` vars only)
4. Figma styles (`Component/Fill/Brand` etc.)

---

## Contracts

- One `.contract.json` per component in `packages/contracts/src/`
- Every contract must pass `pnpm validate` before implementation begins
- Contract `id` is kebab-case, matches the directory name in `apps/web/src/`
- `status` must be `draft` during initial authoring, promoted to `stable` only when
  implementation is complete and tested
- Token paths in the `tokens` section reference Tier 3 component tokens (e.g. `button.fill.brand`)
- Run `pnpm validate` after every contract change — never skip this

---

## Tokens

- **Never use raw values in CSS.** Every value must reference a CSS custom property from `@ds/tokens`
- Custom properties follow `--ds-{token-path}` with dots replaced by hyphens
  (e.g. `--ds-button-fill-brand`, `--ds-accordion-text-trigger`)
- If a value you need doesn't exist as a token, add it to `packages/tokens/src/` first,
  rebuild, then use it
- Never add one-off values to component CSS files
- Run `pnpm tokens:build` after any token file change and confirm the CSS output is correct

---

## Implementation (React / `apps/web`)

- Use `class-variance-authority` (CVA) for all variant-to-class mappings
- CVA variant keys must match contract prop names and values exactly
- Use `clsx` for conditional className merging
- Component props interface must be named `{ComponentName}Props` and exported
- Always use `forwardRef` — components must forward refs to their root DOM element
- Use semantic HTML — don't use `<div>` where `<button>`, `<nav>`, `<section>` etc. is correct
- For complex interaction patterns (accordion, dialog, tooltip, dropdown), use the
  corresponding Radix UI primitive. Never hand-roll focus trapping, keyboard navigation,
  or ARIA state management.
- Component files: `{name}.tsx`, `{name}.css`, `{name}.stories.tsx`, `index.ts`

---

## Fonts

- Token layer owns font **values** — `--ds-font-family-sans`, `--ds-font-family-mono`
- Each app entry point owns font **loading** and **application**:
  - Web/Storybook: import `@fontsource/inter` and `@fontsource/jetbrains-mono` in `preview.ts`,
    set `font-family` on body via `global.css`
  - Web Components demo: import fontsource CSS in demo entry point
  - iOS: bundle Inter in Xcode, reference in `Info.plist`
  - Android: `res/font/` or Downloadable Fonts API
- Never import fonts in component CSS files
- Never put `@font-face` or `@import` font rules in `@ds/tokens`

---

## Icons

- Use Lucide as the icon provider across all web targets until `@ds/icons` exists
  - React: `lucide-react`
  - Web Components: `lucide-static`
- Never use one-off inline SVGs in component implementations
- iOS: use SF Symbols as interim; Android: use Material Symbols as interim
- The icon contract uses `type: "ref", ref: "icon"` — platform-agnostic

---

## Accessibility

- Every contract must declare `accessibility.wcagLevel` — minimum `AA`
- Every component must have a declared ARIA `role` in its contract
- Keyboard interactions must be listed in `behavior.keyboardShortcuts`
- The `@storybook/addon-a11y` panel must show 0 violations before a component is done
- Focus management must follow the contract's `accessibility.focusManagement` declaration

---

## Storybook Stories

- Stories live in `{name}.stories.tsx` alongside the component
- Every contract variant must have a corresponding named story — no exceptions
- Story names match contract variant `displayName` values exactly
- Contract metadata (description, usage do/dont, version, status) is piped into
  Storybook docs — never write docs by hand in stories
- Interaction tests (`play` functions) are required for any story involving user interaction
- All stories must pass the a11y addon before merge

---

## Schema changes

- If a contract requires a field not in the schema, update `packages/schema/schema.json` first
- After any schema change, run `pnpm types:generate` to regenerate TypeScript types
- Document schema changes in `docs/decisions.md` as a new ADR
- Schema changes are breaking if they remove or rename existing fields — bump major version

---

## Versioning

- Use `pnpm changeset` to record changes before merging to main
- Contracts, schema, and tokens are linked — a breaking schema change bumps all three
- Never manually edit `CHANGELOG.md` files — changesets manages this

---

## CI

- All PRs must pass: `validate-contracts` → `build-tokens` → `test-web`
- Never merge with a failing CI run
- If you add a new package or app, add it to the CI workflow

---

## Branching

- Token architecture changes, contract updates, CSS updates, and Figma library
  generation are one feature — they ship together on the same branch
- Never update Figma variables/components without a corresponding codebase
  commit in the same PR. The contract is the source of truth; Figma is derived.

---

## Common workspace issues

If `pnpm install` throws `ERR_PNPM_WORKSPACE_PKG_NOT_FOUND`, the package name
field has been corrupted. Fix with:

```bash
sed -i '' 's/"@component-contracts\/schema"/"@ds\/schema"/' packages/schema/package.json
sed -i '' 's/"@component-contracts\/contracts"/"@ds\/contracts"/' packages/contracts/package.json
```

All packages in this workspace use the `@ds/` scope. Never use `@component-contracts/`.

---

## What not to do

- Don't write component CSS with raw values — always use `--ds-*` custom properties
- Don't create a component without a contract
- Don't reference Tier 1 or Tier 2 tokens directly in components — always go through Tier 3
- Don't write Storybook docs by hand — derive them from the contract
- Don't hand-roll keyboard navigation or focus management for complex components
- Don't merge contracts with `status: draft` to main without a plan to implement
- Don't skip `pnpm validate` before pushing contract changes
- Don't update Figma without a matching codebase commit

---

## Figma library — architecture

### Token architecture (3 tiers)

- **Primitives collection** — raw values, single "Value" mode. Mirrors `packages/tokens/src/primitive/`
- **Semantic collection** — aliases into Primitives. Mirrors `packages/tokens/src/semantic/`
- **Component paint styles** — named `Button/Fill/Brand`, `Accordion/Text/Trigger` etc.
  Raw hex values mirroring Tier 3 component tokens. Applied via `fillStyleId`/`strokeStyleId`.
- Components bind spacing/sizing/typography to Semantic variables via `setBoundVariable`
- Components bind colors via paint styles — not variable bindings
- Figma is always downstream of contracts — never modify Figma without a contract change first

### Canvas organization

- Each component gets its own dedicated **page**: "Buttons", "Accordion", "Cards" etc.
- Within each page, use a Figma **Section** (`#` prefix in layers) to contain all
  component sets for that component
- Section name matches the component name exactly
- Never put multiple unrelated components on the same page
- Never create separate pages per variant — one page per component

### Naming conventions

- Variables use `/` as group separator matching W3C DTCG: `color/blue/500`, `space/md`
- Component sets use `/` for asset panel grouping: `Button/Primary`, `Accordion/Trigger`
- The component name before `/` matches the contract id in PascalCase
- Sub-components use the parent name as prefix: `Accordion/Trigger` not just `Trigger`
- Never create a component set without a `/` prefix — ungrouped components
  are invisible in the assets panel
- Variant frame names use key=value format: `"Size=Medium, State=Default"`
- Component property names match contract prop names exactly: `variant`, `size`, `state`
- Component set description:
  `"Source: {id}.contract.json v{version} | {slot/variant}\nTokens: {Component}/* → Semantic → Primitives"`

---

## Figma library — evaluate_script

### Script requirements (non-negotiable)

- **Plain JavaScript only** — no TypeScript annotations, no type casts, no interfaces
- **Always wrap in the async IIFE pattern:**
  ```javascript
  (async () => {
    try {
      // all code here
    } catch(e) {
      figma.closePluginWithFailure(String(e && e.message || e))
    }
  })()
  ```
- Use `figma.root.children.find(n => n.type === 'PAGE' && n.name === 'X')` — NOT `figma.pages.find()`
- `figma.closePlugin()` takes a **string** argument:
  `figma.closePlugin(JSON.stringify(result))` ✓
  `figma.closePlugin({ message: ... })` ✗
- Script character limit is ~20,000 — minify by removing comments if needed
- **Always one script, never incremental** — multiple scripts leave partial state

### Non-negotiable execution order

Every script that creates components must follow this phase order:

1. **Cleanup** — delete existing nodes/styles matching the component name
2. **Fonts** — `await figma.loadFontAsync()` for EVERY weight before creating ANY node
3. **Variable lookups** — build lookup maps for Primitives and Semantic collections
4. **Paint styles** — create all `Component/*` styles with raw hex values
5. **Create nodes** — set raw values for layout, padding, colors
6. **Apply paint styles** — `fillStyleId`, `strokeStyleId`
7. **Bind variables** — `setBoundVariable` for spacing, sizing, typography
8. **Set explicit modes** — call `setModes()` recursively on EVERY node
9. **Size focus rings** — AFTER components have real dimensions
10. **Layout on canvas** — position, wrap in background frames, create Section
11. **Validate** — check `width/height > 0`, return `errors` array

### Variable modes — the #1 silent failure

Every variable collection gets a ghost empty mode (all values = 0) alongside the named
"Value" mode. Components default to the ghost mode, so ALL variable bindings resolve
to 0 unless you explicitly set the mode.

**Always use this helper and call it on every node and every child:**

```javascript
function setModes(node) {
  try { node.setExplicitVariableModeForCollection(primitivesCol.id, primMode.modeId) } catch(_) {}
  try { node.setExplicitVariableModeForCollection(semanticCol.id, semMode.modeId) } catch(_) {}
  if ('children' in node && node.children) {
    for (const c of node.children) setModes(c)
  }
}
```

Call `setModes(comp)` after creating each component AND on focus ring nodes.

### Font loading — the reliable pattern (critical)

Global `loadFontAsync` is necessary but NOT sufficient. Font must also be asserted
directly on each text node before setting characters.

**The only reliable order — enforce this inside `makeText()` everywhere:**

```javascript
await figma.loadFontAsync({ family: 'Inter', style: 'Medium' }) // global load first
t.fontName = { family: 'Inter', style: 'Medium' }               // assert on node
t.fontSize = 16                                                   // set size
t.characters = 'your text'                                        // set characters LAST
```

Never set `characters` before `fontName` and `fontSize`. Violating this order causes
text nodes to silently collapse to `width=0, height=0`, which causes `combineAsVariants`
to produce malformed component sets.

Inter style strings (confirmed): `"Regular"`, `"Medium"`, `"Semi Bold"` (with spaces).

### Fixed-width, hug-height components

Never use `resize(width, smallNumber)` — the hardcoded height overrides
`counterAxisSizingMode = 'AUTO'` permanently.

```javascript
// Correct pattern:
comp.layoutSizingHorizontal = 'FIXED'
comp.layoutSizingVertical = 'HUG'
comp.resize(320, comp.height)  // fixes width, preserves current height
```

### `setBoundVariable` — correct property names

These shorthand properties do NOT exist and throw silently:
- `cornerRadius` → use `topLeftRadius`, `topRightRadius`, `bottomLeftRadius`, `bottomRightRadius`
- `strokeWeight` → use `strokeTopWeight`, `strokeBottomWeight`, `strokeLeftWeight`, `strokeRightWeight`

These work: `paddingTop`, `paddingBottom`, `paddingLeft`, `paddingRight`, `itemSpacing`, `fontSize`, `fontWeight`

### `layoutSizingVertical` / `layoutSizingHorizontal`

Only valid on auto-layout frames and their direct children. Always guard:

```javascript
if (node.layoutMode === 'VERTICAL' || node.layoutMode === 'HORIZONTAL') {
  node.layoutSizingVertical = 'HUG'
}
```

Use `primaryAxisSizingMode` / `counterAxisSizingMode` instead where possible.

### Paint styles

- `PaintStyle.setBoundVariable` does NOT exist — do not attempt
- Create styles with raw hex values only
- Apply via `node.fillStyleId = styleId` and `node.strokeStyleId = styleId`
- For transparent fills/strokes: `node.fills = []` — do NOT assign a styleId

### Focus rings

- `strokeAlign = 'OUTSIDE'` is clipped by component set bounds — always use `'INSIDE'`
- Set `layoutPositioning = 'ABSOLUTE'` AFTER `appendChild`, never before
- Size the ring AFTER the parent has real dimensions (after font load)
- Call `setModes()` on focus ring nodes

### Auto layout reference

```javascript
// Hug both axes:
node.primaryAxisSizingMode = 'AUTO'
node.counterAxisSizingMode = 'AUTO'

// Fixed width, hug height:
node.layoutSizingHorizontal = 'FIXED'
node.layoutSizingVertical = 'HUG'
node.resize(320, node.height)

// Child stretches to fill parent width:
child.layoutAlign = 'STRETCH'

// Child fills remaining space:
child.layoutGrow = 1
```

### Component sets

Frame names must use key=value format before combining: `"Size=Medium, State=Default"`

After `combineAsVariants`, always configure layout on the set:

```javascript
set.layoutMode = 'HORIZONTAL'
set.layoutWrap = 'WRAP'
set.itemSpacing = 16
set.counterAxisSpacing = 16
set.primaryAxisSizingMode = 'AUTO'
set.counterAxisSizingMode = 'AUTO'
set.fills = []
```

### Validation pattern

Always end every script with a validation block:

```javascript
const errors = []
for (const comp of set.children) {
  if (comp.width === 0 || comp.height === 0) errors.push(comp.name + ' collapsed')
}
figma.closePlugin(JSON.stringify({ childCount: set.children.length, errors }))
```

### Known Alpha limitations (March 2026)

- `PaintStyle.setBoundVariable` — not available
- `componentPropertyDefinitions` — throws on sets with existing errors
- Variable collections — always create a ghost empty mode alongside named modes
- No visual feedback during execution — validate dimensions programmatically
- Script character limit ~20,000 chars — minify if needed, never split into multiple calls
- All limitations subject to change as the Alpha matures
